Brant---

You can rub, and buff, and wax, but like you think, the finish just
won't last that long for the amount of labor involved.

Just painted a Chevy Van for a customer, and the material alone cost
$725.00 for PPG Concept single stage white.

Green my cost a little more beause of the pigment's needed to create the
color---

Break the piggy bank and pop for the paint job----your satisfaction will
be your reward.

Later,

Terry


 
